<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/kha_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/kha_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Eugene, OR 7/18/2002<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=3367'>Nathan "Bib Fortuna" Russell</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=3367&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> July 18, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Yes, it is yet another Thursday night LOTR tournament at Addictive Behaviors (plug: www.addictive-behaviors.com). We became sanctioned with an unprecedented 11 players today, which is a great sign for future tourneys. Several new faces showed up, all of whom I wanted the opportunity to play, because it gets rather old playing Mark all the time.<br>
<br>
Game 1 vs Dena Garrison&#39;s Isengard deck.<br>
<br>
I win the bid 4-2 and get out the Pony. I have Aragorn in my starting hand, so I play him as well as No Stranger To The Shadows. I move on to Site 2, Breeland Forest. She plays an Isengard Servant there. He takes an archery wound, then Aragorn beats him in a fight. I move to 3, Council Courtyard, and she plays another Servant. Another archery wound goes on the new Servant, then Aragorn beats the surviving one from the last site. Arwen + Defiance makes short work of the second one. I make it to Site 3 unscathed, which rocked. <br>
<br>
She starts with Gandalf TGP, and she also has Aragorn in her starting hand, as well as Boromir, Glamdring. Aragorn&#39;s Bow, Ranger&#39;s Sword and Blade Of Gondor. What is up with that? She moves to 2 with 17 in the pool. I play Orc Commander and a Troop Of Uruk-hai. Boromir gets assigned to the Troop, and Aragorn on the Commander. She makes a boo-boo and uses the Blade to wound the Troop, then the Troop wins the fight and Boromir dies. Aragorn takes 1, and the Orc Commander deals 3 more. She stops.<br>
<br>
I play Calaglin and move to Hollin, where she plays yet another Isengard Servant. You should know the routine by now: He takes 1 archery, then Aragorn beats him into submission. Calaglin wounds him once to finish him off, then I double to the Bridge. I wasn&#39;t expecting a Balrog here, as most people don&#39;t use the Balrog unless they play Moria. I was sorely mistaken. I had no pumpers, so Arwen and Legolas both died. :(<br>
<br>
She heads to the Sanctuary, and I can&#39;t do anything with the little twilight she gave me, so I play nothing. I discard a Shadow card, trying to get more FP stuff, but no luck. I move to Site 6, and she plays the common Saruman and an Uruk Brood. Aragorn + Swordsman wounds the Brood and Calaglin finishes him off. Here I make a huge mistake and decide to move again, as I have no wounds on me. I don&#39;t know what I was thinking when I chose to double move, but it was my undoing. She plays two Isengard Smiths, both strength 8, and since I had no pumpers for Frodo, he got overwhelmed.<br>
<br>
Pros: Killing Boromir early.<br>
Cons: I really need to get more sleep if I keep on making such stupid mistakes like that.<br>
<br>
Game 2 vs...BYE!<br>
<br>
Grr, that loss put me into the losing column, and as luck would have it, I was the last card remaining.  I can tell that I won&#39;t be winning this tournament. <br>
<br>
Game 3 vs Vince Roberts&#39; Uruk deck.<br>
<br>
I lose the bid 3-2, and he starts with uncommon Boromir and Mr. Took. He gets out Aragorn with the Pony, and a Hobbit Sword and There And Back Again on Frodo. He moves to Midgewater Marshes, exerting Frodo and Pippin. I play an Isengard Retainer and One Of You Must Do This. Aragorn + Swordarm Of The White Tower wounds the Retainer, and he moves again, and I play an Uruk Rager. Aragorn gets assigned to the Retainer again, then Frodo gets assigned to the Rager. Boromir exerts and Frodo plays a Dagger Strike to win, and Aragorn takes a wound.<br>
<br>
On my turn, I play Aragorn and No Stranger, and a Frying Pan on Frodo, and that&#39;s it. I move, exerting Frodo, and he plays an Uruk-hai raiding Party. He takes an archery wound, then Aragorn fights and takes 2. I move again, and he can&#39;t afford any other minions. Legolas directs his archery to kill off the Uruk.<br>
<br>
He heals up and moves to Hollin, where I play a Troop Of Uruk-hai. Aragorn gets assigned to him, and I play a Lurtz&#39;s Battle Cry to deal 3 wounds to Aragorn. He stops. I play an Elven Bow on Arwen, and move to Hollin. He plays another Troop Of Uruk-hai, whom he exerts to play Worry, then my archery picks him off. I stop there. He moves to the Bridge, and I play Lurtz and an Uruk Rager. The Rager gets assigned to Frodo, and another Dagger Strike/Boromir combo kills him off. Lurtz eats Pippin for lunch. He stops there. <br>
<br>
I play Celeborn and Gondor Bowmen and move to the Bridge and face the common Balrog, but I&#39;m prepared for it this time. Aragorn + Swordsman keeps him alive, and 2 Defiances on Arwen do the same. I double to the Sanctuary, and he plays an Uruk Captain, an Uruk Slayer and an Uruk-hai Raiding Party. I direct my archery to kill the Slayer, then assign Celeborn to the Raiding Party and Frodo on the Captain, as anyone else would die to the Captain&#39;s damage +1 text. He then plays a Bred For Battle, bringing the Captain&#39;s strength up to 12, overwhelming Frodo&#39;s meager 5 strength.<br>
<br>
Pros: Um, smooshing Pippin?<br>
Cons: Losing a game to yet another stupid mistake. I should have simply killed Arwen at that point, but I didn&#39;t and died. :(  Remind me to get more sleep before next week&#39;s tournament.<br>
<br>
Game 4 vs Guy Garrison&#39;s Nazgul/Gandalf deck.<br>
<br>
He bids 3 while I bid 0. He starts the Pony and gets out Aragorn (this sounds familiar). He puts Glamdring on Gandalf and Armor on Aragorn and then moves. I play an Isengard Servant, and Gandalf beats him into submission. He moves again, and I play an Uruk Rager. Aragorn gets assigned to the Rager, and plays Sentinels Of Numenor to win, then Gandalf finishes off the Servant.<br>
<br>
On my turn, I get out Aragorn, Athelas, Elrond, Haldir and Calaglin, then use Elrond to draw 3 more cards. I then play Sam and move out. He plays Nelya, converts my site into Weatherhills, then plays Morgul Gates + non-twilight Witch-king. Legolas picks off Nelya, then Aragorn takes on the Witch-king twice. I move again, and he plays Cantea. Arwen + Defiance wounds Cantea, then I send Sam against the Witch-king, having served his purpose. On the fierce, Aragorn and Arwen each take wounds.<br>
<br>
He heals, then plays Boromir, and he moves to Hollin. I play Isengard Retainer and a Troop Of Uruk-hai. Aragorn plays Swordsman to take on the Troop, and Gandalf beats the Retainer. He stops there.<br>
<br>
I heal, play Thrarin and move to Hollin. He drops Cantea again, and Arwen + another Defiance defeats him. I use Calaglin to finish Cantea off, then I move to the Bridge, where the common Balrog shows up. I throw Thrarin in front of the Balrog (nobody tosses a Dwarf? Huh?), then Haldir dies as well.<br>
<br>
On his turn, he plays Armor on Boromir and moves. I play another Troop and an Orc Commander. I use One Of You Must Do This to deal a couple wounds to his Fellowship. A Servant reduces the Troop so that Boromir beats him, then another Servant reduces the Commander for Gandalf. I use the Commander to deal 1 more wound, then he stops.<br>
<br>
I head for the Sanctuary, and I run into a Morgul Gates + Attea. Arwen and Aragorn each jump in front and take 1 each. I stop there. He plays Sam and a Ranger&#39;s Sword, removes some burdens and moves. I play an Orc Overseer and an Isengard Servant, and Gandalf takes 1 from the Overseer, while Aragorn beats the Servant. The Overseer then exhausts Gandalf, and he stops there.<br>
<br>
I move to Site 7, where he plays Cantea and 2 Morgul Skulkers. Aragorn beats 1 Skulker, Legolas loses to the other, and Arwen takes 2 from Cantea. I stop. He heals, plays a Flaming Brand, moves to 7, and I play a Retainer, an Uruk Brood and Cantea. Cantea unfortunately gets assigned to Aragorn, so he drops both of the weapons. Gandalf beats the Retainer, and Boromir takes 1 from the Brood. He doubles to 8, and I play Enquea. He assigns Cantea to Aragorn, the Retainer to Frodo, the Brood to Boromir and Inky to Gandalf. A wel-timed Hobbit Stealth prevented Frodo from being overwhelmed, and everyone else lives, albeit badly wounded.<br>
<br>
I play Boromir, Last Alliance and a Flaming Brand on Aragorn, then move on. He plays a Skulker and Enquea. Arwen beats Inky once, then takes 1 on the fierce. Boromir takes 1 from the Skulker, and I double to 9. He plays Nelya, Toldea and Ferny. I play Banner Of The White Tree on Aragorn, and he takes on Toldea, Nelya and Ferny. Boromir gets assigned to the Skulker again, and Legolas fights Inky. On the fierce, Aragorn fights Nelya and Toldea again, then Arwen dies to Inky.<br>
<br>
Pros: Finally winning, and getting Aragorn up to 18 strength.<br>
Cons: Having too many dead guys at the end.<br>
<br>
So I ended up in 5th place out of 11, which is really horrible for me. I really need to get more sleep before I play in my next tournament.<br>
<br>
Also, this was Mark Apker&#39;s last tournament for about 2 years, and I didn&#39;t get a chance to play him. But he took second place, which is good for him. I wish you luck in whatever you may be doing on your mission trip, Mark! <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3849&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
